                    "body": "Assigning and unsetting fix version priority until this issue has been reviewed.",
                    "updateAuthor": {
                        "self": "http:\/\/fw02.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/user?username=wil",
                        "name": "wil",
                        "displayName": "Wil Sinclair",
                        "active": true
                    },
                    "created": "2008-02-25T13:33:52.000+0000",
                    "updated": "2008-02-25T13:33:52.000+0000"
                },
                {
                    "self": "http:\/\/fw02.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/comment\/20522",
                    "author": {
                        "self": "http:\/\/fw02.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/user?username=jokke",
                        "name": "jokke",
                        "displayName": "Joakim Nyg\u00e5rd",
                        "active": true
                    },
                    "body": "I couldn't agree more - a standard library (or framework) should not, ever, silence errors on it's own (unless, possibly, they can be handled gracefully). I spent almost half an hour looking for the culprit, nummerous misplaced @s in Zend_Db_*. It makes it almost impossible to debug. \n\nOn top of this, the @ operator slows things down a great deal as this is what really happens:\n\n$old = ini_set(\"error_reporting\", 0); \n...\nini_set(\"error_reporting\", $old);\n\nSince I removed the @s in Zend for my current project, I could easily produce a patch if needed.",
                    "updateAuthor": {
                        "self": "http:\/\/fw02.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/user?username=jokke",
                        "name": "jokke",
                        "displayName": "Joakim Nyg\u00e5rd",
                        "active": true
                    },
                    "created": "2008-03-28T16:08:41.000+0000",
                    "updated": "2008-03-28T16:08:41.000+0000"
                },
                {
                    "self": "http:\/\/fw02.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/comment\/20763",
                    "author": {
                        "self": "http:\/\/fw02.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/user?username=letssurf",
                        "name": "letssurf",
                        "displayName": "James Dempster",
                        "active": true
                    },
                    "body": "Grr I just spent over an our trying to work out why my script died on $myTable->createRow($data);\n\nIt turns out my _rowClass object had a parse error in it cause I was implementing a interface that didn't quite match fully. But the dam @Zend_Loader::loadClass($this->_rowClass); on line 1126 of Zend_Db_Table_Abstract stopped me from seeing the parse error!\n\nHope this will get fixed soon.",
                    "updateAuthor": {
                        "self": "http:\/\/fw02.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/user?username=letssurf",
                        "name": "letssurf",
                        "displayName": "James Dempster",
                        "active": true
                    },
                    "created": "2008-04-09T09:49:55.000+0000",
                    "updated": "2008-04-09T09:49:55.000+0000"
                },
